WHEREAS, Parker plans to pursue a degree in political science at either Tulane
University or Louisiana State University and to continue his education by earning a law
degree, with the goal of serving the people of the state of Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, inspired by his grandmother's military service and supported by his
parents, Darrel and Jessica Posey, Parker remains deeply rooted in his Holden High School
community and he embodies the values of service, integrity, and leadership.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby commend and congratulate Parker Posey on being selected the 2025-2026
"Student of the Year" at Holden High School in Livingston Parish.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
Parker Posey.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
